Located in the historic and scenic suburb of Newlands, at the foot of Table Mountain, Newlands Peak is a residential development comprising a total of 232 units spread over 11 floors. Also Read: 76 Corlett Drive Development in Melrose North, Johannesburg, South Africa The units include micro and studio apartment units, one and two-bedroom apartment units, one and two-bedroom premium apartment units, and three-bedroom penthouse units with sizes ranging respectively from 29m2 – 45m2 and 38m2 – 47m2, 43m2 – 64m2 and 80m2 – 104m2, 66m2 – 72m2 and 100m2 – 138m2, and 141m2 – 192m2.  The development features an impressive lobby with 24hr concierge security, high-speed fiber connectivity (activated by owner), coffee shop & restaurant, meeting rooms, room service from restaurant & coffee shop, cleaning services, drop and collect laundry in the foyer, rooftop entertainment decks surrounded by greenery and with 2 heated rooftop pools, loungers, day beds, gas braais, and pergolas. It also has a state-of-the-art gym, yoga deck and running trail, communal green leafy atrium with Wi-Fi, seating, meeting areas, tranquil reading area on the 4th floor, on-site building manager, and pet-friendly setting.  Safety is beefed up with top-of-the-line security with biometric access controls, electronic guest sign-in, private access-controlled elevator to the lobby and stores, and access control & 24HR CCTV surveillance throughout the reception, parking, gym, and lobby areas. Newlands Peak is developed by Rawson Developers, the property development division of the Rawson Property Group, which is a nationwide property organization founded back in 1982.